  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Postoperative pulmonary complications following abdominal surgery are frequent and
      associated with increased morbidity and mortality and hospital length of stay. Pressure
      controlled ventilation will improve oxygenation indices , hemodynamics during anesthesia for
      laparoscopic colectomy, decreasing postoperative pulmonary complications.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
